A #TrumpShutdown means that popular 7(a) and 504 loans would cease to be issued. In the 7(a) program alone, a shutdown would reduce capital to small firms by $110 million per day.

A #TrumpShutdown prevents federal agencies from entering into any new contracts, including those with small businesses. On a daily basis, a shutdown could cause small firms to forgo approximately 6,875 contract actions worth $301,656,083.
